---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import portraitAbout from '../assets/portrait-about.jpeg';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Sven Read"
  description="Sven Read, Senior Product Designer near Munich. 20+ years across complex B2B systems, regulated environments, industrial IoT, and AI-first products."
>
  <article>
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 md:px-10 pt-32 md:pt-40 lg:pt-48 pb-16 md:pb-20">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-12 md:gap-20 items-start">
        <div class="w-56 md:w-72 lg:w-96 shrink-0">
          <Image
            src={portraitAbout}
            alt="Portrait of Sven Read"
            widths={[280, 400, 600, 800]}
            sizes="(max-width: 768px) 224px, (max-width: 1024px) 288px, 384px"
            class="w-full h-auto rounded-2xl"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent mb-6">
            About
          </p>
          <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl leading-[1.05] tracking-tight">
            Hi, I'm <strong>Sven</strong>.
          </h1>
          <p class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-muted mt-8 max-w-2xl leading-snug">
            Senior Product Designer near Munich. 20+ years across surgical software, building automation, energy infrastructure, and AI-first products.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 md:px-10 mb-20 md:mb-28">
      <div class="space-y-6 font-sans text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          My work tends to sit at the same edge: where a technical user — a <strong>surgeon</strong>, an <strong>installer</strong>, a <strong>data center operator</strong>, a <strong>home inspector</strong> — depends on the interface to make consequential decisions. The design challenge is rarely about making something look modern. It's about removing the friction between what someone needs to do and what the software lets them do, while making sure they can trust what they're looking at.
        </p>
        <p>
          I bridge design and engineering directly. I prototype in production code — <strong>React, HTML/CSS, Tailwind</strong> — and work with development teams from concept through ship. AI-native tools (Cursor, Claude) are part of the daily workflow, used for speed, not novelty.
        </p>
        <p>
          I've co-founded two companies. <strong>Om7Sense</strong>, an energy management platform for data centers, was acquired by Schleifenbauer Group in 2023. <strong>Aeyes</strong>, an AI-powered inspection reporting tool, is current — I'm acting CEO and sole designer. In between, I led design at Brainlab (surgical navigation software), built a design system from scratch at Vaillant Group (HVAC and building automation), led teams at BörseGo (fintech), and contracted via Toptal for clients including Saudi Aramco, Boston Consulting Group, and McDonald's New Zealand.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 md:px-10 mb-20 md:mb-28">
      <div class="border-t border-hairline pt-12 md:pt-16">
        <h2 class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-10">
          Background
        </h2>
        <dl class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-y-10 gap-x-12">
          <div>
            <dt class="font-display text-lg mb-3">Current</dt>
            <dd class="font-sans text-base text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Co-Founder & Product Designer, <strong>Aeyes</strong><br />
              Senior Product Designer, <strong>Baind</strong> (AI building automation)<br />
              Senior UX Designer, <strong>Toptal</strong> (enterprise contract work)
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-display text-lg mb-3">Previously</dt>
            <dd class="font-sans text-base text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Senior Product Designer, <strong>Vaillant Group</strong><br />
              Lead UX Designer, <strong>Brainlab</strong><br />
              Senior Product Designer, <strong>Cliqz AG</strong><br />
              Design Lead, <strong>BörseGo AG</strong><br />
              Co-Founder, <strong>Om7Sense</strong> (acquired)
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-display text-lg mb-3">Notable clients</dt>
            <dd class="font-sans text-base text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Saudi Aramco<br />
              Boston Consulting Group<br />
              McDonald's New Zealand<br />
              Schleifenbauer Group
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 md:px-10 mb-20 md:mb-28">
      <div class="border-t border-hairline pt-12 md:pt-16 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-y-10 gap-x-12">
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-6">
            Languages
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base text-muted leading-relaxed">
            <strong>German</strong> (native)<br />
            <strong>English</strong> (native)<br />
            French (basic)
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-6">
            Education
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base text-muted leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Interaction Design Specialization</strong><br />
            UC San Diego (Coursera), 2015<br /><br />
            <strong>Nielsen Norman Group UX Certification</strong><br />
            2012–2016
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-6">
            Toolbox
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Figma · Sketch<br />
            React · TypeScript · Tailwind<br />
            Cursor · Claude<br />
            Flutter
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 md:px-10 mb-32">
      <div class="border-t border-hairline pt-12 md:pt-16">
        <p class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl leading-snug">
          I'm currently exploring senior, staff, and principal IC roles — where I can stay close to the work, lead with craft, and operate without people management overhead. If that sounds like a fit,
          <a href="mailto:me@svenread.com" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4 decoration-1">get in touch</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
